sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1899008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It does not solely come from genomic sequence. BBa_E0240 come from iGEM Part Registry standard BioBricks while the promoter is from a research paper named Genomic mining of prokaryotic repressors for orthogonal logic gates.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: With all the essential elements for a circuit to function, this part could be used independently in the project to estimate the promoter stength of the phlFp. Since it contains a green fluorescence protein reporter gene, GFP protein would be produced during the characterisation, thus, the intensity of the GFP could be used to estimate the phlFp promoter strength and compare it to that of the other two promoters in our project, lacp and tetp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We have to think of the characterisation method for it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM16_Hong_Kong_HKUST

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1899004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PphlF is a constitutive promoter. repressed by phlF repressor(K1725040) induced 2,4-Diacetylphloroglucinol ( DAPG ) inducer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since it is a new promoter, forward and reverse oligos of PphlF with XbaI and PstI sticky ends were designed and ordered, which were subsequently phosphorylated and annealed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM2016_HKUST

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
